27#include <sys/cdefs.h>
28__KERNEL_RCSID(0, "$NetBSD: nouveau_prime.c,v 1.2 2018/08/27 04:58:24 riastradh Exp $");
29
30#include <drm/drmP.h>
31#include <linux/dma-buf.h>
32
33#include "nouveau_drm.h"
34#include "nouveau_gem.h"
35
36struct sg_table *nouveau_gem_prime_get_sg_table(struct drm_gem_object *obj)
37{
38 struct nouveau_bo *nvbo = nouveau_gem_object(obj);
39 int npages = nvbo->bo.num_pages;
40
41 return drm_prime_pages_to_sg(nvbo->bo.ttm->pages, npages);
42}
43
44void *nouveau_gem_prime_vmap(struct drm_gem_object *obj)
45{
46 struct nouveau_bo *nvbo = nouveau_gem_object(obj);
47 int ret;
48
49 ret = ttm_bo_kmap(&nvbo->bo, 0, nvbo->bo.num_pages,
50 &nvbo->dma_buf_vmap);
51 if (ret)
52 return ERR_PTR(ret);
53
54 return nvbo->dma_buf_vmap.virtual;
55}
56
57void nouveau_gem_prime_vunmap(struct drm_gem_object *obj, void *vaddr)
58{
59 struct nouveau_bo *nvbo = nouveau_gem_object(obj);
60
61 ttm_bo_kunmap(&nvbo->dma_buf_vmap);
62}
63
64struct drm_gem_object *nouveau_gem_prime_import_sg_table(struct drm_device *dev,
65 struct dma_buf_attachment *attach,
66 struct sg_table *sg)
67{
68 struct nouveau_bo *nvbo;
69 struct reservation_object *robj = attach->dmabuf->resv;
70 u32 flags = 0;
71 int ret;
72
73 flags = TTM_PL_FLAG_TT;
74
75 ww_mutex_lock(&robj->lock, NULL);
76 ret = nouveau_bo_new(dev, attach->dmabuf->size, 0, flags, 0, 0,
77 sg, robj, &nvbo);
78 ww_mutex_unlock(&robj->lock);
79 if (ret)
80 return ERR_PTR(ret);
81
82 nvbo->valid_domains = NOUVEAU_GEM_DOMAIN_GART;
83
84 /* Initialize the embedded gem-object. We return a single gem-reference
85 * to the caller, instead of a normal nouveau_bo ttm reference. */
86 ret = drm_gem_object_init(dev, &nvbo->gem, nvbo->bo.mem.size);
87 if (ret) {
88 nouveau_bo_ref(NULL, &nvbo);
89 return ERR_PTR(-ENOMEM);
90 }
91
92 return &nvbo->gem;
93}
94
95int nouveau_gem_prime_pin(struct drm_gem_object *obj)
96{
97 struct nouveau_bo *nvbo = nouveau_gem_object(obj);
98 int ret;
99
100 /* pin buffer into GTT */
101 ret = nouveau_bo_pin(nvbo, TTM_PL_FLAG_TT, false);
102 if (ret)
103 return -EINVAL;
104
105 return 0;
106}
107
108void nouveau_gem_prime_unpin(struct drm_gem_object *obj)
109{
110 struct nouveau_bo *nvbo = nouveau_gem_object(obj);
111
112 nouveau_bo_unpin(nvbo);
113}
114
115struct reservation_object *nouveau_gem_prime_res_obj(struct drm_gem_object *obj)
116{
117 struct nouveau_bo *nvbo = nouveau_gem_object(obj);
118
119 return nvbo->bo.resv;
120}
